{
  "text": "A zero-point shear strain \u2202u y /\u2202z \u2243 k m U zpf , where k m and U zpf represent a wavenumber and an amplitude of the zero-point motion of the SAW, is experimentally obtained along with the equations (1) and (2). Using the SAW wavelength of \u03bb SAW = 40 \u00b5m, we finally find U zpf = 0.5 \u00d7 10 \u22122 fm, while a theoretical estimation derived from a value reported in [CITATION_1] , along with the effective mode area of the SAW resonator of \u03c0 \u00d7 100 \u00b5m \u00d7 110 \u00b5m, yields U zpf = 1 \u00d7 10 \u22122 fm. The theoretical value is compatible with the experimentally estimated value, taking into account a large uncertainty accompanied by the calibration of N SAW .",
